    Filter that checks if a data object is inside a period of time. The period is specified by the start and end in TimeFilter.TimeFilterData.

    Data is restricted to the following types: Instant, LocalDateTime, LocalDate, Date and all classes that implement the TemporalAccessor interface. Strings are supported and parsed. You can specify the pattern for parsing in the filters options. Default is DateTimeFormatter.ISO_LOCAL_DATE_TIME.

    Request Data:
    start - 2015-01-01T01:00:00
    end - 2015-01-31T23:59:59
    Options:
    pattern - 'd MMM uuuu' for '3 Dec 2011', details in DateTimeFormatterBuilder.appendPattern(String)
